<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INSTRUMENTS - 1000 SERIES From 01/01/1998 to 02/07/2004 - TROUBLESHOOTING - WARN ENGINE INDICATOR</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>WARN ENGINE INDICATOR</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Do not probe the ECM connectors with metal leads as it could damage the connector. Always use a
                    Hickok 60 pin breakout box (ZTSE-4445) to test ECM related circuits.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <table id="t0820608" frame="all">
            <title>Warn Engine Indicator</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <colspec colwidth="0.65in"/>
                <colspec colwidth="0.63in"/>
                <colspec colwidth="1.40in"/>
                <colspec colwidth="0.79in"/>
                <colspec colwidth="0.81in"/>
                <colspec colwidth="1.01in"/>
                <colspec colwidth="1.39in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Step</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Key</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Action</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Test Points</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Yes - In Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>No - Out of Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect ECM conn. (379) and connect wire harness conn. to breakout box. Use a test
                                jumper to connect pin 55, circuit 97T to ground. Move key switch to ignition position.
                                Does warning light illuminate?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Warning light illuminates.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Warning light circuits test good. Turn key off, reconnect conn. (379), and turn key
                                on. If warning light does not illuminate during bulb check, reprogram/ replace ECM.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove instrument cluster and remove "warn engine" light bulb. Test bulb for
                                continuity.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Across warning light bulb.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;100 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Re-install bulb. Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace defective bulb and reconnect connector. If problem persists, repeat all
                                tests.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (28). With jumper still attached to the breakout box, measure
                                resistance from pin 15 of wire harness conn. (28), circuit 97T to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Conn. (28)/ pin 15, cir. 97T to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97T, conn. (3), or circuit 97T, then repair.
                                Reconnect connectors.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect wire harness connector (27). Move key switch to ignition position and
                                measure voltage from pin 10, circuit 28 to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Conn. (27)/ pin 10, cir. 28 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12&#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (27). Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 28 from fuse F13, then repair. Reconnect
                                connectors.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With jumper still connected to breakout box, reconnect conn. (28). Does warning light
                                illuminate?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Warning light illuminates.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Warning light circuits test good. Reconnect conn. (379).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace defective cluster assembly. Reconnect connector.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
